E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: Peri finds comfort in Tom as sparks fly during their date. Sienna decides to do whatever it takes to escape. And a shocking theory about Robbie's whereabouts leaves residents heartbroken.

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Good, the Sad and the Drugly: A volunteer inspires Bart to become a better person. Lisa writes an essay about what Springfield will be like in 50 years' time. (S20 Ep17/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Looking for a love match this time are a self-proclaimed 'man-eater', a urologist whose job can scare off men, and a single mum seeking a guy who can accept that she has a child. (S17 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: Married at First Sight UK
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series: More strangers get wed, but will a frosty first impression leave one bride out in the cold? And will there be harmonious honeymoons for our fresh newly-weds? (S10 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: Bring It!
E4Plus1.uk.description: Demanding dance coach Miss D and her elite Dancing Dolls prepare for a fierce competition, but will spotty performances and personal scraps prematurely scupper their chances? (S1 Ep1)

Film4.uk.title: Die Hard
Film4.uk.description: (1988) Action-thriller with Bruce Willis and Alan Rickman. Can a New York cop free the hostages being held in a skyscraper by an arch villain? Yippee ki-yay... whoops, can't say that here.

Film4.uk.title: Ravenous
Film4.uk.description: (1999) Darkly comic horror with Guy Pearce and Robert Carlyle. In 1840s California, an American soldier with a taste for human flesh struggles to stay clean in the face of bad influence.

Film4.uk.title: Kind Hearts and Coronets
Film4.uk.description: (1949) This dark comedy from Ealing studios sees Alec Guinness take on the roles of eight characters, all the noble victims of a vengeance-seeking relative, played by Dennis Price.

Film4.uk.title: Think Like a Dog
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Cheeky comedy with Megan Fox. A young science prodigy (Gabriel Bateman) invents a piece of tech that lets him and his pet dog communicate with each other telepathically.

Film4.uk.title: Dunston Checks In
Film4.uk.description: (1996) Comedy starring Faye Dunaway and Rupert Everett. A hotel owner's attempt to upgrade her star rating is undermined by the arrival of a master thief and his light-fingered orangutan.

Film4.uk.title: Secret Headquarters
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Family comedy with Michael Pea. A young lad discovers that his slacker dad is a superhero. And before he's got used to the idea, he must foil a villain's plot to bring his dad down.

Film4.uk.title: Fisherman's Friends
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Heart-warming comedy based on the real-life story of the Cornish folk ensemble who took the UK charts by storm in 2010, starring Daniel Mays and Tuppence Middleton.

Film4.uk.title: Wild Card
Film4.uk.description: (2015) Sin City thriller with Jason Statham. A compulsive gambler who does favours for money just wants out of the Vegas life. Just one big win at the tables should do it...

Film4.uk.title: Glass
Film4.uk.description: (2019) M. Night Shyamalan directs an all-star cast in this genre-bending superhero sequel. Three superhumans team up to escape a psychiatric ward. With Bruce Willis in a cagoule.

Film4.uk.title: Benjamin
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Simon Amstell's bittersweet comedy romance stars Colin Morgan as a young filmmaker angsting over his second feature when he falls for a French music student.

Film4.uk.title: LumoTV: Sign2Win
Film4.uk.description: Relationships are put to test as colleagues, sisters, and a married couple battle it out for 1,000. Will their nerves hold up under the pressure of these five games? [SL]

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: The Winslow Boy
Film4.uk.description: (1948) Anthony Asquith's drama based on a famous 1912 court case with Cedric Hardwicke as the father of a boy accused of theft who pursues the case to the highest courts. With Robert Donat.

Film4.uk.title: The 300 Spartans
Film4.uk.description: (1962) Historical drama with Ralph Richardson. A retelling of the stand made at Thermopylae in 480 BC by a small Greek force against invasion by an enormous Persian army.

Film4.uk.title: The Devil at 4 O'Clock
Film4.uk.description: (1961) Drama. Spencer Tracy stars as an unfairly unpopular priest living on a volcanic South Sea island which is about to erupt. With Kerwin Matthews, Frank Sinatra and Barbara Luna.

Film4.uk.title: Midway
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Roland Emmerich's sprawling, action-packed war drama about the Battle of Midway, a major turning point in World War II. Starring Ed Skrein, Luke Evans and Woody Harrelson.

Film4.uk.title: Infinite
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Sci-fi action. Mark Wahlberg discovers that his hallucinations are memories from past lives. There are others like him, but they don't all have good intentions...

Film4.uk.title: Team America: World Police
Film4.uk.description: (2004) Outrageous satirical comedy from the South Park team. A crack team of puppets battle to save the world from an evil terrorist plot hatched by North Korean leader Kim Jong Il.

Film4.uk.title: Antwone Fisher
Film4.uk.description: (2002) Real-life drama with Denzel Washington. In trying to uncover the reason for recruit Antwone Fisher's violence, a naval psychiatrist uncovers a history of child abuse.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: All the King's Men
Film4.uk.description: (1949) Drama with John Ireland. A local politician begins to lust for the kind of power he used to hold to account. He should be careful how he treats people on the way to the top...

Film4.uk.title: Mandy
Film4.uk.description: (1952) Poignant Ealing drama starring seven-year-old Mandy Miller as a deaf girl whose parents - played by Phyllis Calvert and Terence Morgan - fight over her treatment.

Film4.uk.title: The Swimmer
Film4.uk.description: (1968) Burt Lancaster stars as the angst-ridden middle-aged man who decides to swim home via neighbour's pools in Frank and Eleanor Perry's superb allegorical drama.

Film4.uk.title: Footsteps in the Fog
Film4.uk.description: (1955) Atmospheric Victorian melodrama. Stewart Granger plays a sinister aristocrat who poisons his wife. However, his maid (Jean Simmons) knows his secret and tries to use it against him.

Film4.uk.title: Cowboys & Aliens
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Sci-fi western starring Daniel Craig and Harrison Ford. A brutal cattle baron and his amnesiac enemy must cease their feuding when a town is attacked by aliens.

Film4.uk.title: Good Luck to You, Leo Grande
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Drama starring Emma Thompson as a recently widowed, retired teacher who has a sexual bucket list she wants to get around to now that she has the time and, perhaps, even the energy.

Film4.uk.title: Fresh

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet II
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Deep: Creatures that live in volcanic hot spots on the ocean bed, areas that reach temperatures hot enough to melt lead and which may hold the secrets behind all life on Earth. S2 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet II
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Coral Reefs: Creatures that live on coral reefs, including groupers, predators with a grasp of communication that has led scientists to conclude they're as intelligent as chimpanzees. S2 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet II
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Big Blue: Wildlife that live thousands of kilometres from land, featuring footage of baby turtles using debris as life rafts and sperm whales hunting for squid deep beneath the surface. S2 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Wilderness with Simon Reeve
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Kalahari: Simon Reeve travels across the Kalahari desert in southern Africa, going on a hunt with a group of San trackers before heading to the oasis of the Okavango Delta. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Flipping Bangers
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Toyota MR2: Will and Gus look to make some quick cash as they fix and wrap a Toyota MR2 MK2. It's quick and it's cheap, but it's the lowest spec out there and it looks dowdy. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Granada/Raleigh Chopper: Paul and Charlie pick up a JZR three wheeler speed demon while Dave gets nostalgic over a brace of Raleigh Choppers, a few Honda C90s and a rare Mark 1 Ford Granada. S12 Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash: Restoring Classics
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The team fly the flag for King and country with one of their most luxurious purchases to date - a 1981 Rolls Royce Silver Spirit. S4 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash: Restoring Classics
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The team think they can smell profit by choosing one of the simplest cars ever built, the VW Beetle. S4 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The team opt to buy one of the most affordable sports cars on the road - the Mazda MX-5. S4 Ep3
